called "Krishna Sabrang," which

00:02:05.990 --> 00:02:11.540
is music of our
country, India, through

00:02:11.540 --> 00:02:14.170
our beloved lord Krishna.

00:02:14.170 --> 00:02:17.070
Because Krishna is omnipresent
all over the country.

00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:22.000
And when he's omnipresent,
there are so many cultures,

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:25.470
so many languages, so many
genres of music in India.

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:27.810
So if I can feature
all those in one

00:02:27.810 --> 00:02:30.840
show and having a
common theme of Krishna.

00:02:30.840 --> 00:02:33.690
So somehow [INAUDIBLE]
and Krishna Sabrang,

00:02:33.690 --> 00:02:36.650
it was almost like doing
musical [? seva. ?]

00:02:36.650 --> 00:02:41.210
And coming to the US and singing
popular music, film music,

00:02:41.210 --> 00:02:42.570
is a no-brainer, actually.

00:02:42.570 --> 00:02:44.910
I wanted the people
over here to also listen

00:02:44.910 --> 00:02:47.530
to other forms of music, which
are there in our country, which

00:02:47.530 --> 00:02:52.100
is like classical
music, [INAUDIBLE]

00:02:52.100 --> 00:02:54.004
and all kinds of stuff.

00:02:54.004 --> 00:02:55.170
So we put the show together.

00:02:55.170 --> 00:02:58.150
