00:21:20.540 --> 00:21:23.750
But tell us a little
bit about music

00:21:23.750 --> 00:21:25.040
as a passion and a profession.

00:21:25.040 --> 00:21:26.456
There are so many
people today who

00:21:26.456 --> 00:21:29.500
are aspiring musicians,
who come out there,

00:21:29.500 --> 00:21:31.190
and who perhaps look
at this as to how

00:21:31.190 --> 00:21:32.580
do I make it into a profession.

00:21:32.580 --> 00:21:34.121
What is your word
of advice for them?

00:21:37.382 --> 00:21:38.840
SHANKAR MAHADEVAN:
Firstly, I think

00:21:38.840 --> 00:21:41.180
there are two ways of doing it.

00:21:41.180 --> 00:21:45.230
I would say that what is
it that you want to do?

00:21:45.230 --> 00:21:46.810
What is your ultimate aim?

00:21:46.810 --> 00:21:52.280
Do you want to just
become a popular singer,

00:21:52.280 --> 00:21:57.560
and become a YouTube sensation,
or something like that?

00:21:57.560 --> 00:22:00.530
Or do you want to study music?

00:22:00.530 --> 00:22:06.130
And as a result of which,
your music can become popular.

00:22:06.130 --> 00:22:07.660
So what is it that
you wanted to do?

00:22:07.660 --> 00:22:09.610
Both are valid, actually.

00:22:09.610 --> 00:22:15.730
Because the path that I
took was a difficult path.

00:22:15.730 --> 00:22:19.870
Because I studied
Indian classical music.

00:22:19.870 --> 00:22:24.380
My foundation, the grammar
of, the language of my music

00:22:24.380 --> 00:22:28.280
is classical music,
Carnatic classical music

00:22:28.280 --> 00:22:29.900
is what I studied.

00:22:29.900 --> 00:22:34.310
And I used that as a medium, and
all other forms of music that I

00:22:34.310 --> 00:22:36.020
do, whether I'm
doing film music,

00:22:36.020 --> 00:22:38.960
whether I'm doing fusion music,
whether I'm doing popular

00:22:38.960 --> 00:22:43.310
music, [INAUDIBLE] music, or
[INAUDIBLE] music in south

00:22:43.310 --> 00:22:44.180
India--

00:22:44.180 --> 00:22:47.960
they're all derivatives
of classical music,

00:22:47.960 --> 00:22:50.300
is what I believe.

00:22:50.300 --> 00:22:52.850
But the other way
is, I mean, you

00:22:52.850 --> 00:22:57.270
can become a one hit wonder, or
maybe a two, three hit wonder.

00:22:57.270 --> 00:23:01.790
And you still can make
the same amount of money.

00:23:01.790 --> 00:23:05.495
You can still have the same
amount of hits on YouTube,

00:23:05.495 --> 00:23:11.330
or social media, still
be flying first class,

00:23:11.330 --> 00:23:14.450
and traveling, and doing
your shows and all.

00:23:14.450 --> 00:23:18.860
But it's totally up to you.

00:23:18.860 --> 00:23:22.414
So if you want to approach
the popular route,

00:23:22.414 --> 00:23:23.330
you still can do that.

00:23:23.330 --> 00:23:29.370
But one thing is, you'll always
be unsure of what you're doing.

00:23:29.370 --> 00:23:35.430
You'll not be technically
proficient as to what

00:23:35.430 --> 00:23:38.470
your song is all about, what
is the skill that you use.

00:23:38.470 --> 00:23:41.520
Is it a C major, E minor,
D-- ah, I don't know.

00:23:41.520 --> 00:23:44.730
[? You'll see. ?]
What beat it is,

00:23:44.730 --> 00:23:47.100
what are the chords
that are playing behind?

00:23:47.100 --> 00:23:49.770
Do you want to know that, or
you don't want to know that?

00:23:49.770 --> 00:23:52.380
I mean, end goal
can be the same.

00:23:52.380 --> 00:23:55.620
But how you want to approach
it, what kind of a musician,

00:23:55.620 --> 00:23:59.150
in depth, do you want
depth in your music or no?

00:23:59.150 --> 00:24:01.220
Is what you have to decide.

00:24:01.220 --> 00:24:04.540
And I think, personally,
being a musician--

00:24:04.540 --> 00:24:07.290
I mean, for example, if you
want to become a journalist,

00:24:07.290 --> 00:24:10.140
if your language
is really good, you

00:24:10.140 --> 00:24:12.360
can write a beautiful article.

00:24:12.360 --> 00:24:13.950
And I believe in that.

00:24:13.950 --> 00:24:17.520
So if your grammar of
the language of music

00:24:17.520 --> 00:24:22.040
is very strong, you
are very confident.

00:24:22.040 --> 00:24:24.850
And you know what you are doing.

00:24:24.850 --> 00:24:25.850
You know your direction.

00:24:25.850 --> 00:24:27.410
You know 100%.

00:24:27.410 --> 00:24:29.690
Yes, I have gone a little flat.

00:24:29.690 --> 00:24:31.240
I've gone a little sharp.

00:24:31.240 --> 00:24:34.640
[INAUDIBLE] Everybody feels it
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH],, you know?

00:24:34.640 --> 00:24:35.840
But you don't realize.

00:24:35.840 --> 00:24:38.860
When you learn you
understand, oh, I'm going off.

00:24:38.860 --> 00:24:39.960
This chord is not working.

00:24:39.960 --> 00:24:41.390
This chord is working.

00:24:41.390 --> 00:24:42.950
This rhythm cycle I can do.

00:24:42.950 --> 00:24:44.060
It's interesting.

00:24:44.060 --> 00:24:46.520
So you become a
student of music.

00:24:46.520 --> 00:24:48.620
And you remain a
student of music

00:24:48.620 --> 00:24:50.760
for the rest of your
life, which I feel I am.

00:24:50.760 --> 00:24:53.940
I am a student of music,
which I am going to remain

00:24:53.940 --> 00:24:54.940
till the end of my life.

00:24:54.940 --> 00:24:56.990
I'm learning all the time.

00:24:56.990 --> 00:25:00.140
I think, [NON-ENGLISH]
That is, that is a fun.

00:25:00.140 --> 00:25:03.010
It's like learning any art form.

00:25:03.010 --> 00:25:08.250
And our classical music, Indian
classical music, is so great.

00:25:08.250 --> 00:25:13.100
It's the greatest form of
music in the world, I feel.

00:25:13.100 --> 00:25:19.930
If you learn that, you get
certain musical powers--

00:25:19.930 --> 00:25:25.570
musical powers, which you can
use to fly in any form of music

00:25:25.570 --> 00:25:26.510
that you want to do.

00:25:26.510 --> 00:25:31.210
So I feel that it's better
you learn music properly,

00:25:31.210 --> 00:25:34.130
understand music, do a
deep dive [? yeah. ?]

00:25:34.130 --> 00:25:36.650
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] do
a deep dive, no, why not?

00:25:36.650 --> 00:25:39.760
Learn properly and
enjoy the whole process,

00:25:39.760 --> 00:25:43.310
and be a student for the rest
of your life, is my advice.

